    public interface DomainPlugIn
extends PlugIn
    A simple interface for all domain plug-ins. This extends the basic PlugIn interface and adds a reference to the domain with which the plug-in instance is associated. All of the methods of this interface, with the exception of PlugIn.getName(), are implemented in the infrastructure's AbstractDomainPlugIn class; that class, or one of its derivatives, should be used as the basis of any custom domain plug-in implementations.

    • Method Detail

      • getDomain

        Domain getDomain()

        Gets the domain applicable to this plug-in instance. This is a convenient wrapper for getContainer.

        While a plug-in may be associated with one domain in the domain configuration, it will be inherited by any sub-domains, and one of these sub-domains will be reported to apply to this instance. When a plug-in re-uses another plug-in, then the domain of the first plug-in applies to the second.

        Returns:
        The domain associated with this plug-in.
